<br>
However, there are two things you would want to consider.<br>
<br>
First, if you want the game to be challenging, DON'T level too much. This game is geared towards roleplaying, not powergaming. Personally I enjoy being able to push any monster around as if it was a naughty kitten, but more action-minded people might find it boring.<br>
<br>
Second, if you want to powergame, then you don't want to stick to the skills that give you levels. misc skills add to your stat bonuses, but only if you use them, not if you train them. Each time you level you increase three stats, but how much you increase them depends on how much you have used skills based on that stat. So if you powergame with levels as you only goal you'll end up with bad stats.<br>
<br>
Happy hunting. <p>Love, Edeina<br>
