<br>
If you find a mob that is hitting you a fair amout but isn't doing to much damage, let it beat on you, this will raise your armor skill which will raise your AR (armor rating instead of Armor class) and help you level.<br>
<br>
Always run, your Athletics should go up faster that way.<br>
<br>
Your main Attributes level a lot easier then anything else, so if you have spear as your main attribute and are using long sword you are going to level slower.<br>
<br>
Explore, get lost and just run around the country side. The only draw back to this is if you find an item that you need for a quest later. I ususally loot the item and set it on the ground near the dungeon's door so I can come back and get it if I need it later. I have heard some people have issues with stuff disapearing this way so be careful. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=57177>Venerable Holyan Lightwalker</a>,
